{
  "texts": [
    "The elderly, due to their reduced physiological capacity to regulate body temperature, are particularly vulnerable to these effects (Boudreault et al., 2024).",
    "Similarly, individuals with pre-existing cardiovascular or respiratory conditions face heightened risks, as their bodies are less able to cope with the physiological stress induced by high temperatures.",
    "There is a substantial body of literature examining the various pathways through which climate change adversely affects human health, primarily by exacerbating existing health conditions.",
    "Rocque et al. (2021), for instance, conducted a systematic review of this growing field, and the World Health Organization (WHO) has also placed strong emphasis on the health impacts of climate change.",
    "Despite this recognized importance, our review identified only two studies that specifically address the resilience of health systems to climate-related risks, revealing a significant gap in the literature and underscoring the need for further research in this area."
  ]
}